<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Totally Agree.. PvP Server May Fail for this reason</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Antwon">Antwon</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:01 p.m. 5/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Totally Agree.. PvP Server May Fail for this reason<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1268" TARGET=_self>Melee characters on the PvP server</A> (Angus[CC])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I totally agree with Angus.

<P>I played on test server and now on PvP. Most classes can make level 15 solo, some can make mid 20's solo, but other than that.. solo is about done.
<P>The higher level areas in the game require tanks to do well. I see the commercial PvP ending where the beta PvP is now.. Many have reached 15-20th level and now since they cant really adventure very much simply PK all the time. It would be very unfortunate if the PvP server turns out this way, but it is a real possibility.
<P>High level adventuring requires teamwork and a balanced group. Currently the PvP server completely lacks balanced character class selection and teamwork is hard to come by when 99% of the time you get attacked by others if you go to any sort of neutral area (hehe.. I admit.. I do my share of the attacking)
<P>So.. I guess my point is.. if you are someone who thinks you may enjoy tank type characters and PvP server is interesting to you.. Please.. play that character. If everyone goes with the best individual characters in PvP server.. ultimately.. there will be no PvP server.
<P>Finally.. I travel with an Ogre SK and an Ogre Warrior alot.. One on One they are not great PKers.. but when I am teamed with them.. we usually kick ass versus groups all all spellcasters. For example.. sticking a pet on my necro does no damage when my OSK buddy attacks it and it then turns to him and he takes it out very quick.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
